<p class="subText">From Wıʞıdǝpıɐa, the free encyclopedia</p>
<div style="font-family: Arial;">
On February 17, 2015, at 12:01 a.m. EST, an earthquake approximately at 8.0–8.5 on the <span style="color: #447FF5">moment magnitude scale</span>, theorized <span style="color: #447FF5">intraplate earthquake</span> but currently classified as a geological anomaly, occurred near the city of <span style="color: #447FF5">Charlestown</span> at around Lake Waccamaw. The shaking was only mysteriously felt in <span style="color: #447FF5">Albemarle</span>, while also excepting certain locations nearby the <span style="color: #447FF5">epicenter</span>. By the end of the shaking, those awake experienced a falling sensation for a few seconds. More than 90% of the infrastructure in the city was destroyed, and devastating fires went on for a few weeks. Scoring a maximum <span style="color: #447FF5">Modified Mercalli intensity</span> of XI (Extreme), it is the <span style="color: #447FF5">most powerful earthquake in Albemarle</span> by a high margin.

The earthquake was responsible for the deaths of 2,516 civilians, injured hundreds of hundreds of thousands more, and approximately 28.9 billion dollars in damages. It is <span style="color: #447FF5">the deadliest and costliest earthquake</span> since the <span style="color: #447FF5">1906 San Francisco Earthquake.</span> Many of the victims' bodies were found mysteriously still lying on their beds under the rubbles of their homes and apartments, implying that they had not woken up from the shaking. As Charlestown's infrastructure is not built to withstand earthquakes, and especially of this size, many prominent healthcare centers, cancer research institutes, and laboratories, such as <span style="color: #447FF5">Hawthorne Medical Center</span>, were severely damaged as the result of the earthquake. The event has caused a major halt in medical development in the <span style="color: #447FF5">United States</span> due to numerous amounts of medical research and development being concentrated within the city.
<p class="wiki-header">Earthquake</p>
{| class="article-table" style="margin-top: 0.5rem; float: right; margin-left: 1rem; margin-right: 1rem; margin-right: 0; clear: both; border: solid 1px #c8ccd1; background-color: #f8f9fa; "
|-
| style="border-bottom: none;" |<div style="border: solid 1px #c8ccd1;">[[File:Earfquake2.png|300px]]</div>
|-
